main event: On October 6, 1957, a sighting of a round object with red, green, and white lights moving jerkily up and down occurred for a duration of 30 minutes.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for a significant duration of 30 minutes, allowing for detailed observation.
The object was described as having red, green, and white lights, exhibiting unusual movement patterns.
There was uncertainty regarding the nature of the object, with possibilities including astronomical, balloon, or confirmed aircraft.
The report mentions civilian witnesses in San Diego, California, adding credibility to the sighting.
The witness observed the same object on multiple occasions, indicating sustained and repeated sightings.
